==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|chiefly|UK}} A [[pave]]d footpath at the side of a [[road]].
# {{US}} Any paved exterior surface, as with a road or sidewalk.
# The interior flooring, especially when of stone, of large buildings such as a cathedral.
# The material with which a surface is paved.
#: ''Rioting youths swarmed across a downtown Paris plaza... hurling stones and chunks of '''pavement''' at police...'' [http://www.dailytexanonline.com/media/storage/paper410/news/2006/04/05/WorldNation/Youths.Riot.In.France.To.Protest.New.Job.Law-1782963.shtml?norewrite200608311258&sourcedomain=www.dailytexanonline.com]

